    </mj-section>
    <mj-section background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="
              font-size: 24px; 
              line-height: 1.2; 
              font-weight: 400;
              margin-top: 2px !important; 
            ">
              Huawei corruption scandal</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image border-radius="10px" padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.presidentialsummary.com/email/images/huawei-eu-corruption-probe.png" alt="Huawei storefront with large illuminated signage, with silhouettes of people walking inside. Huawei facing a corruption probe in the EU over lobbying payments." href="https://www.presidentialsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="0px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#A9A7AF">
          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Huawei building.Credits: Kevin Frayer/Getty Images
            </i></p>
        </mj-text>
        
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">Four people have been charged with corruption and criminal organization in an alleged <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #4D3060; color: black;" href="https://link.presidentialsummary.com/ps-20-03-2025-h1-1-cash-for-influence-scheme?source=website" target="_blank">cash-for-influence scheme</a> involving Chinese technology giant Huawei. A fifth person was charged with money laundering but was released under conditions. Authorities also carried out new searches at the European Parliament offices in Brussels. Police had already searched Huawei's headquarters in Brussels, and a day later, the European Parliament temporarily banned Huawei lobbyists from its premises.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5;filter:blur(5px);">The alleged misconduct took place from 2021 to the present day under the premise of commercial lobbying. The investigation revealed incidents involving payments in exchange for political influence. Some of these came as excessive gifts and covered expenses for food, travel, and football match invitations. Huawei said it took the allegations seriously and would “urgently communicate” with investigators.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-spacer height="15px"></mj-spacer>
